\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 120. A. cornutus} Pallas,{\i   Reise}{\b  1}: 499 (1771). Stems up to 40(-100) cm, erect, woody at base. Leaves (3-)5-9 cm; leaflets 4-9 pairs, 10-35 × 1-7 mm, broadly obovate to linear-oblong, appressed-hairy on both surfaces; stipules 3-9 mm, not connate. Peduncles about as long as leaves; racemes 2-4(-5) cm, ovoid, dense, with 10-40 flowers; bracts 3-5 mm, linear. Calyx 7-12 mm, the teeth 1/4-1/3 as long as tube, linear-subulate. Corolla violet; standard 18-20 mm, emarginate. Legume 10-18 × 3-4 mm, oblong, straight, with dense, ascending hairs.{\i   S.E. Europe, from N.E. Bulgaria to S. Ural and W. Kazakhstan}. Bu Rm Rs (C, W, E).
\par

