\pard\f0\fs28 Subgen.{\b  Calycocystis} Bunge. Perennials; hairs medifixed. Leaves imparipinnate. Calyx more or less inflated in fruit; corolla not persistent.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28 A largely Asiatic subgenus, characterized by the strong inflation of the calyx in fruit, but the European representatives show this to only a slight degree. Species {\b 127}-{\b 133} are extremely close to each other, and may also easily be confused with {\b 125} and {\b 126}.
\par

